  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Becoming a model bank in South West Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 1980&#x2019;s, one hundred thirty two (132) banana farmers in Kigarama Sub County came together as a group and formed Kigarama Matooke Twetungye Cooperative Society Limited (KMTSCL). The cooperative society was limited by shares. The purpose of the society was to enable members access the vast and reliable Kampala market for bananas. The society later transformed into a microfinance institution in the names of Kigarama People&#x2019;s Savings and Credit Association (KPSCA). In 2005, this association was transformed into a cooperative society registered in the names of Kigarama People&#x2019;s Cooperative Savings and Credit Society (KPCSCS). KPCSCS&#x2019;s headquarters are presently situated in Kanyeganyegye Trading Centre (TC) and its area of operation covers Sheema, Buhweju, Bushenyi and Mbarara Districts in southwestern Uganda. 

Kigarama People&#x2019;s Cooperative Savings and Credit Society is a member owned organization with the General Assembly being the overall policy organ. The Board of Directors (BODs) in whom the day-to-day running of the MFI is vested, give the strategic direction and oversee operations to ensure that operational guidelines and policies are adhered to. After the BODSs, there are four directorates in charge of finance &amp; budget, education, Human Resource and loans.  Under the directorates, the management team headed by the manager run the MFI according to board guidelines and policies. 

Presently the SACCO provides six different loans products to their 5.582 (Jan. 2014) clients in the form of agricultural loans, commercial loans, development loans, school fees loans, asset loans and emergency/short-term loans.

Kigarama SACCO is well organized and has a good financial situation. Management, staff and Board seem to be very ambitious and are keen on expanding their activities. Therefore, they need a lot of risk-capital (equity) to finance their growth. 

Agriterra could work with Kigarama SACCO for 1 year, to;

-update the current business plan in 2014/2015 with attention to the financial program, generating more profit

-smoothen the access to finance
Access to capital, in order to fulfill market demand of loans: UGX 400 million

-train staff
On working with financial ratios, KPIs and internal control measures

-train Board and staff
Expose the team to best practices in Uganda and a neighbouring country, to develop new products and innovate. More research is to be done in order to meet changing market demand

 -create a network between the 4 branches (5th one is about to start)
This entails the accounting system &amp; Internet network, creating a safe working environment and ensuring management is up-to-date 24/7

-assess the viability of setting up an ATM, and if possible assist in executing it. This would be the first ATM at a SACCO in Uganda
In summary they&#x2019;d like to become a model bank in the area, or even Uganda. Their exposure is large, and they have huge influence in the area, boosting farmer entrepreneurship.

Access to capital, in order to fulfill market demand of loans: UGX 400 million.</narrative>
  </description>
